Citation.sTitle: A study on densities and excess volumes in the (c-butyrolactone + aromatic hydrocarbon) system at various temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: Density of three binary mixtures formed by c-butyrolactone with benzene, or toluene, or ethylbenzene has been determined over the full range of compositions over the temperatures range (293.15 to 353.15) K and the local barometric pressure using a vibrating-tube densimeter. From these experiments, excess molar volumes oV E mP have been calculated. It is found to be negative with a minimum at about the mole fraction of 0.5. Excess volumes were also fitted to a Redlich Kister type equation. Our result shows V E m decreases when temperature increases in the studied systems.
